got_df <- data.frame(got_text) %>% 
  mutate(text_full = str_split(got_text, pattern = '\n')) %>% 
  unnest(text_full) %>% 
  mutate(text_full = str_trim(text_full))
got_tokens <- got_df %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text_full)
got_tokens

TASK Taking this script as a point of departure, apply sentiment analysis on the Game of Thrones. You will find a pdf in the data folder. 1: What are the most common meaningful words and what emotions do you expect will dominate this volume? and 2: Are there any terms that are similarly ambiguous to the confidence above?

ANSWER 1: we expect negative emotions to dominate this volume. The ggplot in code line 156 shows that both negative and positive words are very common. We found in code line 126 that the most meaningful words are love, grand, beautiful, pleased, pleasure, splendid etc.

2: Lord is an ambiguous word, because it has both positive and negative sentiments.
